  {
    "type": "content",
    "mod": "5",
    "tag": "",
    "title": "What Is Jenkins?",
    "body": [
      {
        "card": "",
        "items": [
          "An <strong>automation server</strong> for CI/CD pipelines",
          "Open source, industry standard since 2011",
          "Watches your Git repository for changes",
          "Automatically: builds, tests, reports, deploys"
        ]
      },
      {
        "code": "Git push &rarr; Jenkins detects &rarr; Build &rarr; Test &rarr; Quality &rarr; Report\n                                                        |\n                                              <span class=\"str\">Green: ready to merge</span>\n                                              <span class=\"kw\">Red: fix your code</span>"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "mod": "5",
    "tag": "",
    "title": "The Jenkinsfile: Pipeline as Code",
    "body": [
      {
        "code": "<span class=\"kw\">pipeline</span> {\n    agent any\n    stages {\n        stage(<span class=\"str\">'Build'</span>) {\n            steps {\n                sh <span class=\"str\">'mvn clean compile'</span>\n            }\n        }\n        stage(<span class=\"str\">'Test'</span>) {\n            steps {\n                sh <span class=\"str\">'mvn test'</span>\n            }\n        }\n        stage(<span class=\"str\">'Quality'</span>) {\n            steps {\n                sh <span class=\"str\">'mvn checkstyle:check pmd:check spotbugs:check'</span>\n            }\n        }\n        stage(<span class=\"str\">'Package'</span>) {\n            steps {\n                sh <span class=\"str\">'mvn package'</span>\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}",
        "note": "This file lives in Git alongside your code. Pipeline is versioned just like code."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "mod": "5",
    "tag": "demo",
    "title": "Jenkins in Action",
    "body": [
      {
        "code": " <span class=\"kw\">git push</span> origin main\n      |\n      v\n Jenkins <span class=\"fn\">webhook trigger</span> &mdash; detects new commit\n      |\n      v\n <span class=\"kw\">Stage 1: Build</span>      mvn compile          [<span class=\"fn\">32s</span>]\n      |\n      v\n <span class=\"kw\">Stage 2: Test</span>       mvn test             [<span class=\"fn\">1m 15s</span>]\n      |\n      v\n <span class=\"kw\">Stage 3: Quality</span>    checkstyle + pmd     [<span class=\"fn\">28s</span>]\n      |\n      v\n <span class=\"kw\">Stage 4: Package</span>    mvn package          [<span class=\"fn\">12s</span>]\n      |\n      v\n Result: <span class=\"fn\">GREEN</span> (all stages passed) or <span class=\"str\">RED</span> (failed stage stops pipeline)",
        "note": "A failed stage stops everything. Stage 3 quality violation? Package never runs. That&rsquo;s the point."
      },
      {
        "card": "What you see in the Jenkins dashboard:",
        "items": [
          "<span class=\"fn\">Green row</span> = all stages passed, artifact published",
          "<span class=\"str\">Red row</span> = a stage failed, shows which one and why",
          "<strong>Blue ball</strong> = build is running right now",
          "<strong>Build history</strong> = every push, every result, timestamped"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "desc": "What happens when you <code>git push</code>?"
  },
