  {
    "type": "content",
    "mod": "5",
    "tag": "",
    "title": "GitHub Actions: The Modern Alternative",
    "desc": "Jenkins is what we teach. GitHub Actions is what you will likely use at work. Same concepts, simpler setup.",
    "body": [
      {
        "code": "<span class=\"cmt\"># .github/workflows/ci.yml</span>\n<span class=\"kw\">name</span>: Java CI\n<span class=\"kw\">on</span>: [push, pull_request]\n<span class=\"kw\">jobs</span>:\n  <span class=\"kw\">build</span>:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-java@v4\n        with:\n          java-version: <span class=\"str\">\"21\"</span>\n      - run: <span class=\"str\">mvn clean verify</span>"
      },
      {
        "table": {
          "headers": [
            "Concept",
            "Jenkins",
            "GitHub Actions"
          ],
          "rows": [
            [
              "Pipeline definition",
              "Jenkinsfile (Groovy)",
              ".github/workflows/*.yml"
            ],
            [
              "Trigger",
              "Webhook / polling",
              "<code>on: [push, pull_request]</code>"
            ],
            [
              "Stages",
              "stage('Build') { ... }",
              "<code>steps:</code> list"
            ],
            [
              "Infrastructure",
              "You manage the server",
              "GitHub hosts it (free tier)"
            ]
          ],
          "note": "We teach Jenkins because understanding CI <strong>concepts</strong> matters more than memorizing one tool&rsquo;s YAML syntax. The concepts are identical."
        }
      }
    ]
  },
